<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1518515-do-you-think-raymond-really-was-in-love">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Do you think Raymond really was in love with Anne, or merely scared of getting old alone and wanting a (socially acceptable) companion? Do you think their marriage would've lasted? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1518515'><a id="like_count_community_question_1518515" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1518515?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F61672.Bonjour_tristesse">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1518515-do-you-think-raymond-really-was-in-love">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1518515-do-you-think-raymond-really-was-in-love">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/123353014-franka"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1603363079i/123353014._UY100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/123353014-franka">franka</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think he really loved her but i have to admit that I am also not sure if their marriage would have lasted.<br/>First Raymmond would not need to worry abo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think he really loved her but i have to admit that I am also not sure if their marriage would have lasted.<br />First Raymmond would not need to worry about getting old alone. He has manny friends, love affairs and his daughter to spend time with. Of course that is not a typical way of spending your life as you grow up but this is also representing that new way of life and lifesyle sagan discribes in this novel. Thus he would not be alone when he gets old so from my point of view that would not be a reason for him to decide to marry Anne. <br />As I mentioned in the beginning I belive that he is honestly in love mith Anne eventhough she is different from the women he has been with before but that might exactly be why he likes her. But as Raymond has a rather impulsive, not to responsible way of life, I think you are right to question wheather this marriage would have lasted or not. Because Raymond might feel desire towards an other women wich when he would follow that desire might cause the end of that marriage because Anne expects it to be honest and responsible and not as impulsive and drawn to other love affairs like Raymonds life was before.<br />So to sum up I think Raymond honestly loves Anne but I share your concerns about the chances of that marriage to last. :))<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
