<span id="freeTextContainer11383317545107977075">The French seventeen year-old girl narrator is at once astute AND childish. The dolce vita of youth and leisure is intoxicating, to partake in or merely read about, and her bohemian experiences and attitudes give the work a refreshing polish. This is somewhat of the opposite of &quot;Catcher in the Rye&quot; since Cecile is experienced, active, cool, while Holden Caulfield. has all the naivete of a newborn, is more of a spectator &amp; is simply, when all is said &amp; done, just duh-hull.</span>
  <span id="freeText11383317545107977075" style="display:none">The French seventeen year-old girl narrator is at once astute AND childish. The dolce vita of youth and leisure is intoxicating, to partake in or merely read about, and her bohemian experiences and attitudes give the work a refreshing polish. This is somewhat of the opposite of "Catcher in the Rye" since Cecile is experienced, active, cool, while Holden Caulfield. has all the naivete of a newborn, is more of a spectator &amp; is simply, when all is said &amp; done, just duh-hull.</span>
