<div id="review_1689792166" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1689792166" />
    <a title="Vanessa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25545124-vanessa"><img alt="Vanessa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1505021049p2/25545124.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1689792166?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vanessa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vanessa" href="/user/show/25545124-vanessa">Vanessa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780066211695" href="/book/show/828023.Bonjour_Tristesse">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1689792166" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11827922789334925737">Such an indulgent and decadent read, I found out this novella was written by Francoise when she was 18. It’s remarkable how well it’s written given her age. <br/><br/>It depicts the extravagant lives of rich and privileged Cécile and her Father holidaying for two months on the French Riviera, its frivolous and fabulous so much of the book centres around the sexual adventures of these bored and beautiful people. It’s full of melodrama created by pampered and spoilt teenager Cécile drawn to playing in the g</span>
  <span id="freeText11827922789334925737" style="display:none">Such an indulgent and decadent read, I found out this novella was written by Francoise when she was 18. It’s remarkable how well it’s written given her age. <br /><br />It depicts the extravagant lives of rich and privileged Cécile and her Father holidaying for two months on the French Riviera, its frivolous and fabulous so much of the book centres around the sexual adventures of these bored and beautiful people. It’s full of melodrama created by pampered and spoilt teenager Cécile drawn to playing in the grown up world of her Father. Of course things go askew when Cécile concocts a plan to sabotage her Father’s new relationship. It’s full of scheming and dramatics, it was hard to feel sorry for Cécile as she was very self absorbed to the point of irritation! I don’t think Cécile had a full grasp of her emotions as they were all over the place, I guess that’s the beauty of this book, it’s accurate in its portrayal of a confused 17 year old who’s playing in the world of grownups, things are bound to get bumpy. For all its flaws it was wildly and deliciously entertaining!</span>
  <a data-text-id="11827922789334925737" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


