<div id="review_424406285" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/424406285" />
    <a title="Rowena" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2990642-rowena"><img alt="Rowena" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499471926p2/2990642.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/424406285?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rowena" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rowena" href="/user/show/2990642-rowena">Rowena</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782266195584" href="/book/show/6559185-bonjour-tristesse">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2990642-rowena?shelf=french-lit">french-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2990642-rowena?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2990642-rowena?shelf=lu-en-francais">lu-en-francais</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer424406285" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17605001247499189162">&quot;Goodbye Sadness.&quot; I was drawn to the screen adaptation of this book years ago because of the title and I really enjoyed it. I decided to read this book in French as it&apos;s not too long and therefore didn&apos;t seem too overwhelming to me. <br/><br/>The main character, 17 year old Cecile, was something else! It was interesting to read Cecile&apos;s scheming thoughts, though you can&apos;t help but think what a spoiled brat she is. With a playboy father like Raymond who doesn&apos;t really parent her, I guess it&apos;s not a surpri</span>
  <span id="freeText17605001247499189162" style="display:none">"Goodbye Sadness." I was drawn to the screen adaptation of this book years ago because of the title and I really enjoyed it. I decided to read this book in French as it's not too long and therefore didn't seem too overwhelming to me. <br /><br />The main character, 17 year old Cecile, was something else! It was interesting to read Cecile's scheming thoughts, though you can't help but think what a spoiled brat she is. With a playboy father like Raymond who doesn't really parent her, I guess it's not a surprise. I'm also thinking she had an Oedipus complex. <br /><br />Well-written and very interesting. I plan on reading the English version soon to see if I've missed anything.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17605001247499189162" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

